# Raw authority artifacts are byte-exact by definition (framework spec §7.2).
# Git must never convert their line endings or otherwise touch their bytes;
# the LF->CRLF autocrlf conversion on checkout is exactly the corruption that
# produced non-verbatim "verbatim" evidence in the failed prior attempt
# (WITNESSED-FAILURE-MODES.md #6).
verification/authorities/raw/** -text

# Everything else: LF in every working copy so hashes and locks are
# deterministic across Windows and Linux checkouts.
* text=auto eol=lf
